.TH WS\-AUDIOD 1 "March 2026" "1.0.0" "ws-audiod"
.SH NAME
ws\-audiod \- multi-consumer audio capture daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ws\-audiod
.RB [ \-c
.IR FILE ]
.RB [ \-s
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-D
.IR DEVICE ]
.RB [ \-r
.IR RATE ]
.RB [ \-C
.IR N ]
.RB [ \-b
.IR N ]
.RB [ \-g
.IR DB ]
.RB [ \-p
.IR N ]
.RB [ \-B
.IR SECS ]
.RB [ \-d ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ws\-audiod
provides continuous ALSA audio capture with concurrent multi-consumer access
through a single device interface. Features include ring-buffer clip extraction,
gapless block recording, and zero-copy shared memory distribution.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-c " FILE" "\fR,\fP \-\-config " FILE
Configuration file path.
.TP
.BI \-s " PATH" "\fR,\fP \-\-socket " PATH
Control socket path.
.TP
.BI \-D " DEVICE" "\fR,\fP \-\-device " DEVICE
ALSA device (default: default).
.TP
.BI \-r " RATE" "\fR,\fP \-\-rate " RATE
Sample rate in Hz (default: 48000).
.TP
.BI \-C " N" "\fR,\fP \-\-channels " N
Number of channels (default: 1).
.TP
.BI \-b " N" "\fR,\fP \-\-bits " N
Bit depth: 16 or 24 (default: 16).
.TP
.BI \-g " DB" "\fR,\fP \-\-gain " DB
Input gain in dB (default: 0.0).
.TP
.BI \-p " N" "\fR,\fP \-\-period\-size " N
ALSA period size in frames (default: 1024).
.TP
.BI \-B " SECS" "\fR,\fP \-\-block\-record " SECS
Enable gapless block recording with SECS-second files.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Enable debug logging.
.SH AUTHOR
Ed Baker <ed@ebaker.me.uk>
